face-image: img/redfront.jpg

=  The <span style="color: #000000;">**Center Party**</span> and the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Reichsbanner**</span>
  
Since the founding of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Reichsbanner**</span> in 1924, it has mostly been dominated by politicians from the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, with a bulk of its membership being <span style="color: #c00000;">socialist</span> workers.
However, with the fear of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Reichsbanner**</span> "diluting religious fervour" and the strong disapproval from the clerics, the reaction of the <span style="color: #000000;">**Center**</span> has been lukewarm to say the least. Despite nominal membership from centrists like <span style="color: #000000;">Marx</span> and <span style="color: #000000;">Kohler</span>, enthusiasm for the Reichbanner exists solely amidst ardent republicans such as <span style="color: #000000;">Joos</span> or <span style="color: #000000;">Wirth</span>.
In light of the increasingly volatile political landscape and rise of the miltant <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span>, there has been growing pressure from the left of the party of officially affiliate the <span style="color: #000000;">**Center**</span> with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Reichsbanner**</span>.
However, our socially heterogeneous base might not take kindly to such cooperation with the <span style="color: #c00000;">socialists</span>. Now, as German democracy is under siege, how will we respond to the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>'s overtures?

- @endorse: The <span style="color: #000000;">**Center**</span> officially affliates itself with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Reichsbanner**</span>.
- @reject: Surprisingly, we have rejected the overtures from the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>.

@endorse
subtitle: This is will strengthen the forces of democracy in the fight against <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span>. 
choose-if: z_party_leader = "Joos" or z_party_leader = "Kaas"
on-arrival: pro_republic += 5; spd_right += 1; spd_relation += 5; ddp_relation += 3; ddp_left += 1; z_new_middle += 3; z_catholics += 3; nsdap_workers -= 3; kpd_workers += 2; nsdap_rural -= 2; z_dominance += 5; right_dissent += 7; endorse_seen += 1; rb_strength += 700; rb_militancy += 0.1; z_endorse_rb += 1; dnvp_relation -= 3;

Following the concerning rise of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span and growing disillusion with the <span style="color: #000000;">We</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">im</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">ar</span>, control of the streets is neccessary in combating the militancy of politcal exteremists. Due to our friendly relations with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, we have now encouraged our members to join the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Reichbanner**</span>. The <span style="color: #FF7F00;">Christian Left</span> faction is ecstatic, while the right is in an uproar over this sharp turn to the left and demands we reverse our course at once.

Meanwhile, our youth organisations flock to join the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Reichbanner**</span>, which has significantly bolstered its membership. With the influx of Catholics, the notion of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Reichbanner**</span> being a purely <span style="color: #c00000;">**socialist**</span> militia has been mostly dispelled, giving it legitimacy amongst bourgeois republicans. 


@reject
subtitle: Such a move is a sharp rebuff to the <span style="color: #FF7F00;">Christian Left</span> faction and will be unpopular amongst rank-and-file members.
choose-if: z_party_leader = "Kaas" or z_party_leader = "Stegerwald"
on-arrival: pro_republic -= 3; spd_left += 1; spd_relation -= 5; ddp_relation -= 3; left_dissent += 5; left_labor_dissent += 3; z_workers -= 3; z_new_middle -= 2; nsdap_workers += 3; nsdap_catholics += 1; endorse_seen += 1; ddp_right += 1; rb_strength -= 300; 

Despite our friendly relations with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, our party has decided to rebuff the overtures of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, with this direct repudiation of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**Reichsbanner**</span> causing some from our party to leave. While the Christian Left in the party question our commitment to the <span style="color: #000000;">We</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">im</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">ar</span> system, the Windthorstbund is furious at our inactivity in the face of the growing strength of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span>.
Meanwhile, Catholic <span style="color: #3E88B3;">conservatives</span> are pleased with our commitment to being a party of the center, but others question how we have let cooperation with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> come this far. 

 
